Are bridge courses available new students?,"Yes, bridge courses are available for new students before the semester begins to strengthen basic knowledge."
What is course evaluation method used?,"The course evaluation method includes continuous assignments, internal tests, and final semester examinations."
Is there course orientation program schedule?,"Yes, a mandatory orientation program is conducted at the beginning of the course for all new students."
What is assignment submission deadline policy?,Assignment deadlines are set by individual faculty members. Please check the course portal for specific due dates.
How to upload assignment online portal?,"Log into the student LMS portal, select your subject, and click on the 'Submit Assignment' link to upload your file."
What is assignment format document requirements?,Assignments should generally be submitted in PDF or DOCX format unless your professor specifies otherwise.
Are handwritten assignments allowed submission?,"Handwritten assignments are only allowed if explicitly requested by the faculty. Otherwise, typewritten digital files are required."
What is late submission penalty marks?,"Late submissions typically incur a penalty of 5% to 10% mark deduction per day late, depending on faculty policy."
How many assignments per subject required?,Most subjects require 2 to 3 assignments per semester as part of the internal evaluation.
What is plagiarism policy assignment rules?,Plagiarism is strictly prohibited. Assignments with a similarity index above 20% may be rejected or heavily penalized.
Can assignment be resubmitted corrections?,Resubmission is generally not allowed after the deadline unless the faculty explicitly requests revisions.
What is assignment grading criteria details?,"Assignments are graded based on content accuracy, original research, formatting, and timely submission."
Are group assignments allowed collaboration?,"Yes, group assignments are allowed if specified by the faculty for specific team-based projects."
How to check assignment feedback comments?,You can view faculty feedback and comments on your assignments directly in the LMS grading section.
What is assignment file size limit upload?,The standard file size limit for uploading assignments to the portal is 20MB.
Can parents track assignment submission status?,Parents can track assignment submission status if they have been granted access to the parent portal.
What is assignment evaluation timeline process?,Faculty typically evaluate and post assignment grades within two weeks of the submission deadline.
Are assignments compulsory pass criteria?,"Yes, passing internal assignments is usually compulsory to be eligible to write the final semester exams."
How to request assignment extension approval?,Extensions must be requested directly from the faculty member via email at least 48 hours before the deadline.
What is assignment topic selection guidelines?,Topics are either assigned directly by the professor or must be chosen from an approved syllabus list.
Can assignment be submitted offline mode?,Offline submission is only accepted if the digital portal is down or the faculty has specifically requested hard copies.
What is assignment marking rubric system?,"A marking rubric breaks down the score by introduction, core analysis, conclusion, and referencing formatting."
Are assignments included final grade calculation?,"Yes, assignment scores usually contribute to 20% to 30% of your total final grade for the subject."
What is assignment plagiarism checking tool?,The institution uses Turnitin to automatically check all submitted assignments for plagiarism.
Can students skip assignment submission?,Skipping assignments will result in a zero for that component and may cause you to fail the internal assessment criteria.
What is assignment revision correction policy?,Revisions are only accepted if the faculty opens a 'resubmission window' for the entire class.
Are assignment templates provided institute?,"Yes, official cover page templates and formatting guides are available in the student portal document library."
How to contact teacher assignment clarification?,You can contact your teacher for assignment clarifications during their office hours or via the official college email.
What is minimum attendance percentage required?,Students are required to maintain a minimum of 75% attendance in each subject to be eligible for exams.
How to check attendance status online?,You can view your daily and aggregate attendance status by logging into the student ERP portal.
What is attendance shortage penalty rules?,Students with less than 75% attendance may be detained from appearing in the final semester examinations.
Can attendance be condoned medical reasons?,Shortages up to 10% can be condoned for valid medical reasons if supported by a certified medical document.
How to apply attendance leave approval?,Leave applications must be submitted via the student portal and approved by the Head of Department.
What is attendance calculation method system?,Attendance is calculated as the ratio of classes attended to the total number of classes conducted per subject.
Are online classes attendance counted?,"Yes, logging into online sessions and participating actively is automatically tracked and counted toward your total attendance."
What is attendance marking system biometric?,Attendance for certain labs and campus entry is tracked using your student ID card or biometric fingerprint scanners.
Can parents view attendance report daily?,"Yes, parents can view daily attendance reports using their dedicated parent portal login credentials."
What is attendance defaulter warning policy?,Automated warning emails and SMS are sent to students and parents if attendance drops below 80%.
How many leaves allowed attendance criteria?,You are permitted to miss up to 25% of classes for personal or sick leave without penalty.
What is attendance requirement exam eligibility?,A strict minimum of 75% attendance overall is required to generate your final exam hall ticket.
Can attendance be corrected errors report?,"If marked absent by mistake, you must contact the subject faculty within 48 hours to have the error corrected."
What is attendance tracking mobile app?,You can track your attendance on the go using the official college mobile app available on iOS and Android.
